text: Nicholas John Overhead (born 1942), is a male former athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== He represented England in the 440 yards at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Perth, Western Australia. He was a member of the Watford Harriers Club. ==References== Category:1942 births Category:English male sprinters Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
